onnect developer progress and alert if development appears stalled or not progressing.\",\n      \"enabled\": false,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775783758784,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775789898684,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"every\",\n        \"everyMs\": 900000,\n        \"anchorMs\": 1775783758784\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"session:agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Check Pet Connect developer progress in /root/.openclaw/workspaces/03-development. Focus on whether the developer appears stalled or not making progress. Inspect recent file changes in docs and src/pet-connect, especially IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN_V2.md, HANDOVER.md, prisma/, src/domain/, src/application/, src/infrastructure/, and other new code. If there are signs of progress, stay silent. If developer output appears stalled, inconsistent, or not moving for too long, send a concise alert to Khuowgn with blocker/risk summary and what needs intervention. Do not ask the user questions unless intervention is truly required.\",\n        \"thinking\": \"medium\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 300,\n        \"lightContext\": true\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1775789158825,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 55162,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastDelivered\": false\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"20f15566-d965-48e3-840f-ee1192cee726\",\n      \"agentId\": \"developer\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"name\": \"bootstrap-backup-ui-scale-adjustment-now\",\n      \"enabled\": false,\n      \"deleteAfterRun\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775879641463,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775880332761,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"at\",\n        \"at\": \"2026-04-11T03:53:30.000Z\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"session:driving-system-bootstrap-developer\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Project: teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup\\nActive repo for implementation:\\n- FE: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe\\n- BE: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-be\\n\\nNew user task:\\n\\\"I need to adjust the current system’s overall screen size and font size. On my current window, I have to scale it down to 80% for it to look right, so please help me implement this adjustment.\\\"\\n\\nYou are in the project-scoped developer session for bootstrap-backup. Follow current SOUL/AGENTS rules, including OpenSpec-first for significant work.\\n\\nRequired approach:\\n1. Check whether this UI scaling change is best implemented via root typography/base layout/container scale tokens, not one-off page hacks.\\n2. Because project has OpenSpec available, create or align to minimal OpenSpec change/spec context first if none exists yet.\\n3. Then implement the FE change.\\n4. Prefer system-wide, maintainable adjustment over per-page patching.\\n5. Avoid breaking responsive behavior.\\n6. Verify by running the FE and checking the affected root layout/theme/global CSS files.\\n7. Write/update handover with exact files changed and short rationale.\\n\\nExpected output back to Orbis:\\n- diagnosis of root cause\\n- implementation approach chosen\\n- exact files changed\\n- whether change is global or partial\\n- any risks / follow-up QA notes\\n\\nDo the work now.\",\n        \"model\": \"sonnet\",\n        \"thinking\": \"medium\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 1800\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1775880052010,\n        \"las